  "text": "Cell culture, plasmids and transfection. HEK293 epithelial cells were grown in Dulbecco's modified Eagle's medium (Gibco) supplemented with 10 % (v/v) FBS (PAA). The HPV-18 E6 or E7 genes were cloned under the control of the CMV promoter [CITATION_1] . Plasmids expressing HPV-11 E6 or E7 proteins were kindly provided by Dennis J. McCance (Queen's University, Belfast, UK; [CITATION_2] . Cells were transfected with the indicated constructions, using calcium phosphate precipitation as described by Matlashewski et al. (1987) .",
